Use of *finalize()* methods should be avoided. They are not a reliable mechanism for resource clean up and it is possible to cause problems in the garbage collector by abusing them.

If you require a deallocation call in your object, say to release resources, use an explicit method call. This convention can be seen in existing APIs (e.g. [Closeable][1], [Graphics.dispose()][2], [Widget.dispose()][3]) and is usually called via try/finally.

    Resource r = new Resource();
    try {
        //work
    } finally {
        r.dispose();
    }

Attempts to use a disposed object should throw a runtime exception (see [IllegalStateException][4]).


